abstract: Twitter is banning many political ads. Here are some that never made it onto the platform.

abstract: Citing harassment allegations at the network, Cory Booker, Kamala Harris, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren urged its parent, Comcast, to conduct an independent review.
snippet: Citing harassment allegations at the network, Cory Booker, Kamala Harris, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren urged its parent, Comcast, to conduct an independent review.
lead_paragraph: For Democratic presidential candidates, this week’s debate in Atlanta comes with the political equivalent of home field advantage: A lead sponsor is the cable network MSNBC, whose liberal-leaning talk shows are as mandatory on the campaign trail as diners in Des Moines.

headline_main: 4 Democratic Candidates Push NBC on Eve of Debate
headline_print_headline: 4 Candidates Join Push for a Review Of NBC’s Workplace

abstract: Joseph R. Biden Jr. has durable support from a multiracial coalition of working-class voters who view him as one of their own.
snippet: Joseph R. Biden Jr. has durable support from a multiracial coalition of working-class voters who view him as one of their own.
lead_paragraph: WEST POINT, Iowa — They are white and nonwhite alike, prefer Facebook over Twitter, if they are on social media at all, and can be hard to find at Democratic campaign events dominated by activists from the professional class. But these blue-collar voters could go a long way toward determining who captures the Democratic presidential nomination — and Joseph R. Biden Jr. is racing to press his advantage with that constituency.

abstract: Despite relatively modest support nationally, Ms. Gabbard has delighted Republicans, independents and conservative Democrats who dislike the Clintons.
snippet: Despite relatively modest support nationally, Ms. Gabbard has delighted Republicans, independents and conservative Democrats who dislike the Clintons.
lead_paragraph: Sitting at a bar in the coastal New Hampshire city of Portsmouth, Ray Brunelle rattled off the qualities he admires in Representative Tulsi Gabbard of Hawaii.

abstract: We followed Ayanna Pressley and Abigail Spanberger as they figured out Washington, forged alliances on the Hill — and clashed with their own party.
snippet: We followed Ayanna Pressley and Abigail Spanberger as they figured out Washington, forged alliances on the Hill — and clashed with their own party.
lead_paragraph: There are not many people whom Abigail Spanberger lets boss her around, but one of them, somehow, is Lois Frankel, a 71-year-old, 5-foot-3 four-term congresswoman from Florida who has a way of waving away protestations with a brisk, cheerful air, somewhere between “Don’t be ridiculous” and “This’ll be great.”
